==English==

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/ˈbɝɡəˌmɑt/}}
* {{a|RP}} {{IPA|/ˈbɜːɡəˌmɒt/}}

===Etymology 1===
{{etyl|fr}} {{term|bergamote|lang=fr}}, from {{etyl|it}} {{term|bergamotta|lang=it}}; probably a corruption of {{etyl|tr}} {{term|bey armudu||a lord's pear|lang=tr}}.

====Noun====
{{en-noun|s|-}}

# {{botany}} A tree of the Orange family ({{taxlink|Citrus|genus}} {{taxlink|bergamia|epithet}}), having a roundish or pear-shaped fruit, from the rind of which an essential oil of delicious odor is extracted, much prized as a perfume. Also, the fruit. 
# {{botany}} Either of two species of the mint family (Europe: {{term|Mentha|genus}} {{taxlink|aquatica|epithet}}, variety {{taxlink|glabrata|variety epithet}}; America: {{taxlink|Monarda|genus}} {{taxlink|didyma|epithet}}).
# The essence or perfume made from the fruit.
# A variety of pear.
#: {{rfquotek|Johnson}}
# A variety of snuff perfumed with bergamot.
#: ''The better hand . . . gives the nose its '''bergamot'''.'' —[[w:William Cowper|William Cowper]].

